## Integration with Other Rules

This rule is **Step 2** of the Mandatory Agent Workflow. See `.cursor/rules/agent-workflow-mandatory.mdc` for complete workflow.

This rule works alongside:
- **Mandatory Agent Workflow:** This is Step 2 (pre-work checklist, after North Star check)
- **North Star Alignment:** Step 1 must be completed first (plans must align with North Star)
- **MA Process Mandatory Rule:** Plans for mathematical/algorithmic work must follow MA Phases 1-5
- **Notebook-First Mandatory Rule:** Code must originate in notebooks, tested and debugged before extraction
- **Change-Approval Protocol:** Step 3 requires plan reference in approval request
- **Action Log Requirement:** Step 5 requires logging plan reference
- **Execution Plan Updates:** Step 6-7 requires updating `Operations/EXECUTION_PLAN.md` when milestones/tasks affected

---

## Enforcement

**MANDATORY:** This rule applies to:

- All Codex agents (via `AGENTS.md` and `docs/codex/CODEX_OPERATING_RULE.mdc`)
- All Cursor AI assistants (via `.cursor/rules/`)
- All external agents accessing the repository
- All automated systems performing work

**Verification:**
- Before any write operation, verify plan reference exists
- If no plan reference, stop and create plan
- Document plan reference in all action logs

